              <img src="//cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/images/smilies/sad.png" alt=":(" title="Frown" /> When I interned in CA in 1997, my roommate was a high school English teacher.  He had some connection to Ray Bradbury and got him to come to the school to speak.  I got to go, and I took along a copy of Fahrenheit 451 for him to sign.  My roommate had a crappy Mazda 323 hatch, and since Ray didn't drive anymore, he drove him home and had him sign the dashboard with a Sharpie.  A great storyteller will be missed.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
